tafsir[18]{c,v,t}:
  83,7,"The matter is not as you thought - that there is no resurrection after death. The book of the people of iniquity from amongst the disbelievers and hypocrites will be in loss in the lower earth."
  83,8,"O Messenger! What will tell you what Sijjin is?!"
  83,9,"Their book is written and will not vanish. Nor will there be any increase or decrease in it."
  83,10,"Destruction and loss on that day will be for those who deny."
  83,11,"Those who deny the day of recompense in which Allah will give His servants the recompense of the actions they did in the world."
  83,12,"None denies that day except every person who transgresses Allahâ€™s limits and commits abundant sins."
  83,17,"Then on the Day of Judgement it will be said to them in rebuke and censure: This punishment that you received is what you used to deny in the world when your messenger told you about it."
  83,18,"The matter is not as you thought - that there will be no reckoning or recompense. The book of the people of obedience will be in Illiyyun."
  83,19,"O Messenger! What will tell you what Illiyyun is?!"
  83,20,"Their book is written and will not vanish. Nor will there be any increase or decrease in it."
  83,21,"This book is witnessed by the angels brought near in every heaven."
  83,22,"Those who do an abundance of good deeds will be in everlasting bliss on the day of judgment."
  83,25,"Their servants will give them wine from sealed containers to drink."
  83,27,"This sealed drink will be mixed from the spring of Tasnim."
  83,29,"Those who committed wrong by the disbelief they held used to mockingly laugh at those who had faith."
  83,30,"When they passed by the believers they would wink at one another in ridicule and amusement."
  83,31,"When they returned to their families they would go back happy with their acts of disbelief and ridicule of the believers."
  83,33,"Allah did not appoint them to guard their deeds so that they could make this statement of theirs."